The press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney, Treasury Under Secretary for International Affairs Lael Brainard, and Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communication Ben Rhodes focused on the discussions and progress made at the G20 summit in Cannes, France. The leaders at the summit were focused on advancing the G20 agenda for achieving balanced and sustainable growth, as well as addressing the pressing challenges in the eurozone. The leaders expressed support for the European plan to stabilize the situation in the eurozone and discussed how the plan would be implemented. The briefing also touched on the role of the European Central Bank (ECB) in the crisis, the exposure of US banks to the eurozone crisis, and the potential need for additional resources for the International Monetary Fund (IMF). Overall, the briefing highlighted the need for political commitment and international support to address the eurozone crisis and promote global economic growth.